nd wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":38,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":47,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John De Peckham IV was born in 1290, in Hadlow, Kent, England, his father, Sir John De Peckham, was 30 and his mother, F, was 15. He married Marjorie De Aldham in 1320, in Sint Jacobiparochie, Friesland, Netherlands. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1345, in Wrotham, Kent, England, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1290–1345":"1290–1345","1300–1327":"1300–1327","1320–1363":"1320–1363","1260–1335":"1260–1335","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1275":"1275","1363":"1363","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Sint Jacobiparochie, Friesland Prov, Netherlands":"Sint Jacobiparochie, Friesland, Madalmaad","Hadlow Manor, Hadlow, Kent, England":"Hadlow, Kent, England","Sint Jacobiparochie, , Friesland, Holland":"Sint Jacobiparochie, Friesland, Madalmaad","Yaldham, Wrotham Park, Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tonbridge, Kent, England":"Tonbridge, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yaldham, Wrotham Par, Kent, England":"Wrotham, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1290–1345":"12